Four suspected burglars were arrested while breaking into an apartment in Kileleshwa. One of the suspects is linked to the theft of cash and electronics from the house of Honda Motors regional boss Hirohide Ichikawa. Kilimani police boss Joseph Muthee said the suspects break into homes while tenants are away. He said they found the suspects with housebreaking tools and some electronic goods. Muthee asked residents whose homes have been broken into to report to the police station. The suspects will be arraigned on Tuesday. Click here for the latest political news